column5: Hey everyone,  Just a heads up...  I came across a site that is clearing out some Live Target lures for 6 or 7 bucks each.  The selection isn't the best, but they still have the crayfish cranks and traps, the pumpkinseed, and some smelts.  Take a look:  http://redrockstore.com/Catalog/index.php?crn=251  Can't go wrong for a lure that usually costs 12 or 13 bucks plus tax up here.
Why, why do you have to do this to me lol. My credit card is still recovering from all the gear I bought over the holidays  I don't own one so i just HAVE TO.
any frogs? dont show Mercer....he may try to kiss em....lol
Those Pumpkinseed are so tempting, as are the crawfish.  I own a few of them already, and have had quite a bit of success with the pumpkinseed.
I bought there Blueback Herring 4 1/2" swimbait, looks amazing...Can't wait to see it swim. Would like to try out there lipless cranks.

I am curious about their lipless crankbaits as well.  I have never had much success with liplless crankbaits, so I have been hesitant to buy these ones at their regular price.  And I think my wife is on high alert with respect to my fishing purchases... so even at this price, it would be iffy...
